<br>
One of my best in game friends decided to quit EQ a few months ago. His last action in Norrath was to allow another Necro friend to sacrifice him down from level 54 to 46.<br>
Of course, 2 months later, he is back in game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The problem is that now, after some grinding, he's level 49, but the rest of the guild is 55+, even 60+. <br>
He's not the kind of guy who enjoys sitting on his arse on a static spawn just to grind, he'll always prefer a death with laughters.<br>
So, knowing that, and knowing I'm a 60 wizard with low-medium gear, I was wondering where we could hunt together to speed up his leveling while having fun. Ideally, I'm looking for a zone where mobs will be green to me so that he can get all the benefit of the kills. We could probably have a 45 chanter with us too.<br>
<br>
Any suggestion?<br>
<br>
Thank's <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23101">Turielaen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Level 60 High Elf Sorceress<br>
Figment<br>
Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3462<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 1:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice needed: how to PL a SK?</span><hr size=1> &gt;Ideally, I'm looking for a zone where mobs will be green to me so that he can get all the benefit of the kills. We could probably have a 45 chanter with us too.<br>
<br>
You will still take your share of XP on green mobs, it will just get thrown away. Your best bet is find a place with good XP and group, or tell him to FD while you quad higher level mobs and just let him share the XP. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arcanist - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eternalwrath.org"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Eternal Wrath</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=turielaen>Turielaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 1:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice needed: how to PL a SK?</span><hr size=1> Oh crap, I feel like a noob, level 60 and I didn't know about the fact I would get my share of exp on green mobs and it would be lost <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
However, I was also thinking that green mobs to me would have not so many HP, which would make it easier to nuke them into oblivion in not time <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23101">Turielaen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Level 60 High Elf Sorceress<br>
Figment<br>
Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zarbonius>Zarbonius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 1:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice needed: how to PL a SK?</span><hr size=1> well, if the chanter doesn't mind memblurring a bit..  <br>
<br>
Try quadding some mobs down to about 5-10% health, then get the chanter to peel off and memblur one at a time.  get your SK buddy to finish off that last 5%, and voila, full XP for him.<br>
<br>
Ooh, and make sure you're not grouped with him at the time, or this won't work.  Memblur might have to be cast a couple of times to make sure it actually clears the mob's aggro, too.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3465<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 1:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice needed: how to PL a SK?</span><hr size=1> &gt;Ooh, and make sure you're not grouped with him at the time, or this won't work. Memblur might have to be cast a couple of times to make sure it actually clears the mob's aggro, too.<br>
<br>
Actually, I do this a bit when powerleveling some of my characters, missed the Enchanter part when I read it the first time. Anyways, pick on mobs that will run when you do enough damage so you can snare em and beat em down easy. Then, root them (use the 30 second root), and have the chanter memblur. Use TFlux staff to aggro them again, if you get their aggro message at this point, you are good to go. If not, repeat the memblur,flux staff thing til you do. At that point, all your damage has been erased and they just need to do 1 point or more of damage to get the XP for it. <br>
<br>
Also, your best bet for max XP is to pick mobs that are red for them and blue for you. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
